%N A396525 Walk along the hexagonal spiral, with its cells numbered starting at 0, as in A395362. Place a (Glinski) queen at each unoccupied cell not attacked by an existing queen. Sequence lists cells occupied by queens.
%H A396525 Jonas Karlsson, <a href="/A396525/b396525.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..19999</a>
%H A396525 Jonas Karlsson, <a href="/A396525/a396525.png">Illustration of the first 19 queens</a>
%H A396525 Jonas Karlsson, <a href="/A396525/a396525_1.png">Scatterplot of the first 200 queens</a>
%e A396525 The zeroth cell is not threatened by any queen, so a queen is placed there, hence a(0) = 0. This queen threatens all cells between 1 and 18 inclusive, but not cell 19, hence a(1) = 19.
%Y A396525 Cf. A396294-A396296 (Glinski Queens of two colors).
